<h1>Privacy Policy — FoodTracker</h1>
<p class="muted">Last updated: 9 June 2026</p>

<p>
This Privacy Policy explains how FoodTracker (“the App”, “we”, “us”),
developed by Boris Serzhanovich, handles your information. The App is a
nutrition, diet, and calorie tracking application for iOS. By using the
App you agree to the practices described below.
</p>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Category</th><th>Examples</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>Health & Nutrition</td>
<td>Active energy burned, dietary energy consumed, weight, water logs (via HealthKit); meals, custom recipes, and goals you enter</td>
<td>To provide core app functionality: nutrition tracking, daily calorie insights, and goal progression</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Name</td>
<td>The display name you provide during onboarding</td>
<td>To personalize the app experience</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Camera</td>
<td>Live camera feed for scanning food barcodes</td>
<td>To quickly find food items. The camera feed is processed locally on your device and images are never saved or uploaded to our servers</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>User Content</td>
<td>Messages and prompts you send to the AI Coach or AI Chef; custom meal recipes you create</td>
<td>To generate AI responses and personalize your diet plan</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>2. HealthKit Data</h2>
<p>
When you grant permission, the App reads health metrics from Apple HealthKit
solely to display them inside the App and compute nutrition insights. We also write data 
(like water intake or logged activities) to HealthKit if you explicitly allow it. We do
<strong>not</strong> use HealthKit data for advertising or marketing, and we
do not share it with third parties. HealthKit data is processed on your device.
</p>

<h2>3. How Your Data Is Stored</h2>
<p>
  Most of your data — meals, custom recipes, logs, and settings — is created and used
  <strong>on your device</strong>. Depending on the feature, data is stored as follows:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>iCloud sync (Apple CloudKit)</strong> — If you are signed in to iCloud, your
    nutrition data (meals, custom recipes, daily summaries, and weight history) is synced across your devices using your
    <strong>private iCloud account</strong> (CloudKit private database, container
    <code>iCloud.com.borisdev.FoodTracker</code>). This data is stored in your personal
    iCloud space, is governed by
    <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/">Apple’s Privacy Policy</a>, and is
    <strong>not accessible to us</strong>.
  </li>
  <li><strong>Cloud Content</strong> — The App fetches curated Academy articles and Chef Recipes from our cloud database (Google Firebase Firestore). This data is read-only.</li>
  <li>To securely fetch remote configurations and curated content, the App creates an <strong>anonymous account</strong> (Firebase Anonymous Authentication). No email or password is required.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. AI Features</h2>
<p>
When you use the AI Coach or AI Chef features, the text and nutritional context you submit is sent
to our secure backend (Google Cloud Functions) and processed by Google’s
Vertex AI (Gemini) models to generate a response. Requests are protected by
Firebase App Check. Please avoid submitting sensitive personal information in
AI prompts.
</p>

<h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
<ul>
<li>Google Firebase (Authentication, Firestore, Analytics, App Check) — <a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy">Firebase Privacy</a></li>
<li>Google Cloud / Vertex AI (Gemini) — <a href="https://cloud.google.com/terms/cloud-privacy-notice">Google Cloud Privacy</a></li>
<li>Apple HealthKit — data governed by Apple’s on-device frameworks</li>
</ul>

<h2>6. Data Sharing</h2>
<p>
We do not sell your personal data. We do not use your data for tracking across
apps or websites owned by other companies. Your personal diet and health data remains strictly private.
</p>

<h2>7. Account & Data Deletion</h2>
<p>
You can delete your data at any time from <strong>Profile & Settings → Delete Profile & Data</strong>, 
which permanently removes your local data and iCloud synced records. Since the App uses Anonymous Authentication, 
there is no remote user account to delete. This action cannot be undone.
</p>

<h2>8. Children’s Privacy</h2>
<p>
The App is not directed to children under 13 (or the minimum age required in
your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
</p>

<h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
<p>
Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete
your personal data. You can exercise deletion directly in the App, or contact
us using the details below.
</p>

<h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The “Last updated” date
above reflects the latest revision.
</p>

<h2>11. Contact</h2>
<p>
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact us at:
<a href="mailto:foodtrackersupport@gmail.com">foodtrackersupport@gmail.com</a>
</p>

